{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775885821746,"sessionID":"ses_284f52368ffeZ3M6cxRmRqKOly","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0b2730001VYqfLPPiTor1Yx","messageID":"msg_d7b0b14cb001hw7xNBdtB0SALt","sessionID":"ses_284f52368ffeZ3M6cxRmRqKOly","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885865473,"sessionID":"ses_284f52368ffeZ3M6cxRmRqKOly","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0b2dda001Tlx1koCm0P9evu","messageID":"msg_d7b0b14cb001hw7xNBdtB0SALt","sessionID":"ses_284f52368ffeZ3M6cxRmRqKOly","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_ac90f9fc6a354ab29c9c1572","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-042 — Docusaurus Documentation Site Framework\n\n## Purpose\n\nEstablish a Docusaurus-based documentation site framework for the agentcube project to provide a modern, searchable, and versioned documentation platform. This framework will enable the team to maintain comprehensive documentation including API references, tutorials, architecture guides, and contributor guidelines in a scalable and maintainable manner.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Module path** | `docs` |\n| **Language** | TypeScript |\n| **Framework** | Docusaurus 3.x |\n| **Documentation types** | API docs, guides, tutorials, changelog, blog |\n| **Versioning** | Multi-version support for releases |\n| **Deployment target** | Static site generation for GitHub Pages or similar |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- Content authoring for specific documentation pages\n- CI/CD pipeline integration for deployment\n- Search backend configuration (Algolia DocSearch)\n- Custom React components beyond Docusaurus defaults\n- Internationalization (i18n) setup\n- Translation workflows\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Usage |\n|------------|-------|\n| `docusaurus` | Core documentation framework |\n| `@docusaurus/preset-classic` | Classic preset with docs, blog, pages |\n| `@docusaurus/theme-classic` | Default theme |\n| `@mdx-js/react` | MDX support for React in Markdown |\n| `react`, `react-dom` | UI library |\n\n## Design\n\n### Directory structure\n\n```\ndocs/\n├── docusaurus.config.ts          # Docusaurus configuration\n├── sidebars.ts                    # Sidebar configuration\n├── tsconfig.json                  # TypeScript configuration\n├── package.json                   # Node dependencies\n├── package-lock.json\n├── static/                        # Static assets\n│   ├── img/                       # Images\n│   └── favicon.ico\n├── docs/                          # Documentation files (Markdown/MDX)\n│   ├── index.md                   # Landing page\n│   ├── getting-started/          # Getting started guides\n│   ├── guides/                    # User guides\n│   ├── api/                       # API reference\n│   └── contributed/               # Contributor guidelines\n├── blog/                          # Blog posts (optional)\n│   └── index.md\n├── src/                           # Custom React components\n│   ├── css/\n│   │   └── custom.css            # Custom styles\n│   └── pages/                    # Custom pages\n│       └── index.tsx             # Landing page component\n├── versioned_docs/                # Versioned documentation\n│   └── version-1.0.0/\n├── versioned_sidebars/            # Sidebars for versions\n└── scripts/                      # Build/deploy scripts\n    └── build.sh\n```\n\n### Docusaurus configuration\n\n```typescript\n// docusaurus.config.ts\nimport { themes as prismThemes } from 'prism-react-renderer';\nimport type { Config } from '@docusaurus/types';\nimport type * as Preset from '@docusaurus/preset-classic';\n\nconst config: Config = {\n  title: 'AgentCube',\n  tagline: 'Intelligent Agent Runtime Platform',\n  url: 'https://agentcube.io',\n  baseUrl: '/',\n  onBrokenLinks: 'throw',\n  onBrokenMarkdownLinks: 'warn',\n  favicon: 'img/favicon.ico',\n  organizationName: 'volcano-sh',\n  projectName: 'agentcube',\n\n  presets: [\n    [\n      'classic',\n      {\n        docs: {\n          sidebarPath: './sidebars.ts',\n          docVersionSuggestions: true,\n          showLastUpdateAuthor: true,\n          showLastUpdateTime: true,\n        },\n        blog: {\n          showReadingTime: true,\n          blogSidebarCount: 'ALL',\n          blogSidebarTitle: 'All Posts',\n        },\n        theme: {\n          customCss: './src/css/custom.css',\n        },\n      } satisfies Preset.Options,\n    ],\n  ],\n\n  themeConfig: {\n    image: 'img/social-card.png',\n    navbar: {\n      title: 'AgentCube',\n      logo: {\n        alt: 'AgentCube Logo',\n        src: 'img/logo.svg',\n      },\n      items: [\n        {\n          type: 'docSidebar',\n          sidebarId: 'docsSidebar',\n          position: 'left',\n          label: 'Docs',\n        },\n        {\n          type: 'docsVersionDropdown',\n          position: 'right',\n        },\n        {\n          href: 'https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube',\n          label: 'GitHub',\n          position: 'right',\n        },\n      ],\n    },\n    footer: {\n      style: 'dark',\n      copyright: `Copyright © ${new Date().getFullYear()} Volcano.sh`,\n    },\n    prism: {\n      theme: prismThemes.github,\n      darkTheme: prismThemes.dracula,\n    },\n  } satisfies Preset.ThemeConfig,\n};\n\nexport default config;\n```\n\n### Sidebar configuration\n\n```typescript\n// sidebars.ts\nimport type { SidebarsConfig } from '@docusaurus/plugin-content-docs';\n\nconst sidebars: SidebarsConfig = {\n  docsSidebar: [\n    'intro',\n    {\n      type: 'category',\n      label: 'Getting Started',\n      collapsed: false,\n      items: ['getting-started/installation', 'getting-started/quickstart'],\n    },\n    {\n      type: 'category',\n      label: 'Guides',\n      items: [\n        'guides/architecture',\n        'guides/configuration',\n        'guides/monitoring',\n      ],\n    },\n    {\n      type: 'category',\n      label: 'API Reference',\n      items: [\n        'api/agent-runtime',\n        'api/code-interpreter',\n        'api/cli',\n      ],\n    },\n    {\n      type: 'category',\n      label: 'Contributing',\n      items: [\n        'contributed/overview',\n        'contributed/development',\n        'contributed/coding-standards',\n      ],\n    },\n  ],\n};\n\nexport default sidebars;\n```\n\n### Package.json scripts\n\n```json\n{\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"docusaurus\": \"docusaurus\",\n    \"start\": \"docusaurus start\",\n    \"build\": \"docusaurus build\",\n    \"deploy\": \"docusaurus deploy\",\n    \"clear\": \"docusaurus clear\",\n    \"serve\": \"docusaurus serve\",\n    \"write-translations\": \"docusaurus write-translations\",\n    \"write-heading-ids\": \"docusaurus write-heading-ids\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Custom CSS example\n\n```css\n/* src/css/custom.css */\n:root {\n  --ifm-color-primary: #3b82f6;\n  --ifm-color-primary-dark: #2563eb;\n  --ifm-color-primary-darker: #1d4ed8;\n  --ifm-color-primary-darkest: #1e40af;\n  --ifm-color-primary-light: #60a5fa;\n  --ifm-color-primary-lighter: #93c5fd;\n  --ifm-color-primary-lightest: #bfdbfe;\n  --ifm-code-font-size: 95%;\n}\n\n.navbar__title {\n  font-weight: 700;\n}\n\n.admonition {\n  font-size: 0.9rem;\n}\n```\n\n## Impact analysis\n\n### Files created\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` | Docusaurus configuration (~80 lines) |\n| `docs/sidebars.ts` | Sidebar navigation config (~40 lines) |\n| `docs/tsconfig.json` | TypeScript config (~20 lines) |\n| `docs/package.json` | Node dependencies (~40 lines) |\n| `docs/package-lock.json` | Lock file |\n| `docs/static/*` | Static assets (~5 files) |\n| `docs/docs/intro.md` | Introduction page (~30 lines) |\n| `docs/docs/getting-started/*.md` | Getting started guides (~100 lines) |\n| `docs/docs/guides/*.md` | User guides (~150 lines) |\n| `docs/docs/api/*.md` | API reference templates (~100 lines) |\n| `docs/docs/contributed/*.md` | Contributor guidelines (~100 lines) |\n| `docs/src/css/custom.css` | Custom styles (~50 lines) |\n| `docs/src/pages/index.tsx` | Landing page (~80 lines) |\n\n**Estimated total**: ~800 lines\n\n### Files modified\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `.gitignore` | Add docs/build, docs/node_modules |\n| `README.md` | Add docs site link |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| @docusaurus/core | ^3.0.0 | Core framework |\n| @docusaurus/preset-classic | ^3.0.0 | Preset with docs/blog |\n| @docusaurus/theme-classic | ^3.0.0 | Default theme |\n| @mdx-js/react | ^3.0.0 | MDX support |\n| react | ^18.2.0 | React library |\n| react-dom | ^18.2.0 | React DOM |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| Developers | Use docs for onboarding and reference |\n| Users | Self-service documentation |\n| Support team | Reference for troubleshooting |\n| Marketing | Product documentation |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n**Very Low**: This is a new documentation module. No existing code is modified. The documentation site is additive and does not affect the core product functionality.\n\n### Performance characteristics\n\n- **Build time**: ~1-3 minutes for full site\n- **Dev server startup**: ~10-20 seconds\n- **Static site size**: ~10-50MB depending on content\n- **Page load**: Fast with static generation + optional CDN\n\n### Edge cases handled\n\n1. **Broken links**: Docusaurus validates links during build\n2. **Missing images**: Graceful fallback for missing assets\n3. **Version conflicts**: Explicit version management\n4. **Build failures**: Clear error messages for authoring issues\n5. **Mobile responsiveness**: Built-in responsive design\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\n### 1. Use GitBook\n\n**Approach**: Use GitBook platform for documentation.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Proprietary SaaS with limited customization\n- Free tier restrictions on collaborators\n- Less control over hosting and branding\n- Integration requires GitHub OAuth\n\n### 2. Use MkDocs with Material theme\n\n**Approach**: Use MkDocs (Python) with Material for MkDocs theme.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Python-based (team more familiar with Node.js/TypeScript)\n- MDX not supported natively (limited React component embedding)\n- Static site generation less flexible for React integrations\n- Team preference for JavaScript ecosystem\n\n### 3. Use VuePress / VitePress\n\n**Approach**: Use VuePress or VitePress (Vue-based documentation frameworks).\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Vue ecosystem (team works with React)\n- Docusaurus has better integration with React-based projects\n- Docusaurus has mature multi-version support\n- Docusaurus is the standard for Meta/Facebook ecosystem projects\n\n### 4. Use plain Markdown with GitHub Pages\n\n**Approach**: Use raw Markdown files with GitHub Pages (Jekyll).\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Limited navigation and search functionality\n- No built-in versioning support\n- Poor mobile experience\n- Manual navigation structure management\n- No React component support in MDX\n\n### 5. Use Next.js with next-mdx-remote\n\n**Approach**: Build custom docs site with Next.js and MDX.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Significant development overhead\n- Custom implementation required for features Docusaurus provides out-of-box\n- Higher maintenance burden\n- Versioning requires custom implementation\n- Team preference for purpose-built solution\n\n### 6. Use Hugo with Docsy theme\n\n**Approach**: Use Hugo static site generator with Docsy theme.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Go template ecosystem (team not familiar with)\n- MDX support limited\n- Less React integration capability\n- More complex theming customization","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775885865404,"end":1775885865471}}}}
